.5 × 103 L−1 and 2.8 ± 6.9 L−1, respectively, and nearly independent of zn. In contrast to past measurements in mixed-phase clouds combined from many geographical locations where fl increased with temperature, fl decreased from −12° to −3°C as clouds typically consisted of a liquid topped layer with precipitating ice below.},
author = {Fridlind, Ann M. and Ackerman, A. S. and McFarquhar, Greg and Zhang, G. and Poellot, M. R. and DeMott, P. J. and Prenni, A. J. and Heymsfield, A. J.},
